-- Hong Kong shares finish higher, helped by Wall Street's record
-- By Grace Li
-- Fri Aug 22, 2014 04:07AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 22 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares rose on Friday, tracking gains in the U.S. after upbeat economic data sparked a record close on Wall Street.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed up 0.5 percent at 25,112.23 points. It gained 0.6 percent this week. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the top Chinese listings in Hong Kong slipped 0.4 percent for the week, despite a rise of 1.1 percent on Friday.  Among top index boosts, China Petroleum & Chemical Corp <0386.HK> climbed 1.6 percent. It plans a $1.5 billion Hong Kong initial public offering for its oilfield services unit in the first half of 2015, people familiar with the matter told Reuters. [ID:nL4N0QS1OP] Top percentage losers on the Hang Seng fell on  disappointing earnings. China Resources Enterprise <0291.HK> sank 5.6 percent, following Thursday's drop of 2.9 percent, after posting an 8.7 percent decline in first-half net profit.